summary: i hope what happens for endgame is that, for the after credit scene in captain marvel, it says like “some years later”, and...
body:
i hope what happens for endgame is that, for the after credit scene in captain marvel, it says like “some years later”, and carol is in her spaceship just moseying along, and then she hears something on her radio. a distress signal that’s pretty far off, but just understandable. she flies around for a bit, tracing it, and finally she finds it: a ship, free floating in the dark.

she smirks, leaves her ship, and makes her way to the other ship and the distress signal. end of credit scene.

then, a month later, endgame comes out. the first scene is tony in quill’s ship, like he was in the trailer, talking to his suit. the distress signal beeps quietly next to him, but he knows that no one is listening for it.

he slowly runs out of resources and air, and gives up hope. but just when his last bit of air runs out, there’s a tap on the glass outside of the ship.

he looks up to see carol floating there, and she offers him a smile. he sighs in relief, and the title screen rolls: avengers endgame

title: New Captain Marvel TV Spot Focuses on Carol's Past
body:
New Captain Marvel TV Spot Focuses on Carol’s Past

With the marketing campaign going full speed, such as a first-look playing in theaters, Marvel Studios has released a second TV spot for Captain Marvel.

As with most TV spots, there really isn’t much new footage in this one, although there is a quick shot we haven’t seen in the previous trailers. You see Carol in the cockpit of a ship apparently opening fire on something. Could that be what leads…
